definition.value: An N-acyl-L-aspartic acid in which the acyl group is specified as acetyl.
An N-acyl-L-alpha-amino acid anion resulting from deprotonation of both carboxy groups and protonation of the amide nitrogen of N-acetyl-L-glutamic acid.
A dihydroxyflavone that is  chrysin substituted by prenyl groups at positions 6 and 8 respectively.
